      • visible

        public StaticMap visible(StaticMap.GeoPoint... geoPoints)
        Images may specify a viewport by adding visible locations. The visible parameter instructs the Google Static Maps API service to construct a map such that the specified locations remain visible (this parameter may be combined with existing markers or paths to define a visible region as well). Defining a viewport in this manner obviates the need to specify an exact zoom level.
        Parameters:
        geoPoints - to add
        Returns:
        this instance

      • scale

        public StaticMap scale(int scale)
        The scale value is multiplied with the size to determine the actual output size of the image in pixels, without changing the coverage area of the map.
        Parameters:
        scale - 1, 2 or 4 (the later is for Google Maps APIs Premium Plan customers only)
        Returns:
        this instance

      • size

        public StaticMap size(int width,
             int height)
        The size parameter, in conjunction with center, defines the coverage area of a map. It also defines the output size of the map in pixels, when multiplied with the scale value (which is 1 by default).
        Parameters:
        width - in pixels
        height - in pixels
        Returns:
        this instance
